    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The path separator for Windows (`\\`) needs escaping in the string notation, which we worked around using raw string literals `r\"<dir>\\<file>\"`.\r\n\r\nA small example is at https://gist.github.com/tusharpm/ac0eef89796ca9c67ca92fe6c6071f6b.\r\n\r\nIn `mypxd.pxd`, there are two variants of `cdef extern from`:\r\n1. (commented) works - using the escape sequence (`\\\\`).\r\n2. (not commented) uses the `r\"<file_path>\"` notation which results in [an error (attached Output.txt)](https://github.com/cython/cython/files/1357081/Output.txt).",
    "closed_at": "2017-10-07T13:52:51Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "OWNER",
            "body": "According to the code in\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/0.27.x/Cython/Compiler/Parsing.py#L3069\r\nand\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/0.27.x/Cython/Compiler/Parsing.py#L870\r\nthis should actually be supported, although it's probably untested. Coming up with a cross-platform test for this doesn't seem easy...\r\nCould you try to debug that code to see where it goes wrong for you? It should enable `is_raw` in your case and override `kind` with `'u'`, and that should be it.",
